          <title>Social Security recipients get a 2.8% cost-of-living boost in 2026</title>
          <description><![CDATA[WASHINGTON (AP) — The Social Security cost-of-living increase will go up by 2.8% in 2026, which translates to an average increase of more than $56 for retirees every month, agency officials said Friday. The benefits increase will go into effect for Social Security recipients beginning in January.]]></description>
